name: 16S rRNA (cytosine1402-N4)-methyltransferase
reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + cytosine1402 in 16S rRNA = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + N4-methylcytosine1402 in 16S rRNA
comment: RsmH catalyses the N4-methylation of cytosine1402 and RsmI (EC 2.1.1.198) catalyses the 2'-O-methylation of cytosine1402 in 16S rRNA. Both methylations are necessary for efficient translation initiation at the UUG and GUG codons.

references.title: Fine-tuning of the ribosomal decoding center by conserved methyl-modifications in the Escherichia coli 16S rRNA.
